			Le Cinque
			=========

A game for learning beginner Italian vocabulary, five words at a
time.  Play it at https://le-cinque.pages.dev -- buono studio!

CURRICULUM

  Five Italian words are laid out with their English translations
  hidden.  Fill in the letters to reveal all five before you run out of
  mistakes.  Over 1,500 everyday words, most-essential first, so
  beginners meet the core vocabulary soonest.

  Each round leads with words that are due for review, then fills up
  with new ones.  A word comes back on a widening schedule -- one day,
  then three, a week, three weeks, two months -- because retrieving a
  word is what fixes it in memory, and the gap between reviews should
  grow as it sticks.  Getting a word right schedules it just as a miss
  does; a word that stops being tested is a word being forgotten.

  A round never mixes five words from one category (five colors, five
  numbers): closely related words learned together interfere with each
  other.  You only get credit for a word you actually spelled -- a
  correct letter reveals that letter everywhere, so a word can end up
  fully shown without your ever recalling it, and those do not count.

  The reasoning and its sources are collected in RESEARCH.
